  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Replace transfer fluid"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Transfer Fluid Extraction"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "597_4.0_jpn_11582457_4.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "With the vehicle in a horizontal position, remove the drain bolt (A) and drain the transfer fluid."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. Transfer Fluid Refill"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "597_4.0_jpn_11582458_4.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "With the vehicle horizontal, remove the filler bolt (A) and sealing washer (B). Inject the specified ''Honda Genuine Ultra DPSF-II (Dual Pump System Fluid)'' through the filler bolt hole (C) to the same level as the underside of the screw. Designated transfer fluid: Honda Genuine Ultra DPSF-II Transfer fluid volume: When replaced: 0.43L When overhauled: 0.44L Install a new sealing washer and tighten the filler bolt."
    }
  ],
